Rating: 3
One word of advice--use decent vinegar. I tried it the first time with generic balsamic and it was terrible. I knew from the reviews that I had to be doing something wrong, so I got different balsamic vinegar, and that made all the difference in the world. So taste your vinegar before you put it on the strawberries--if it has a really harsh vinegar-y finish, it's not going to go well on fruit.

