Wow. Somehow balsamic makes strawberries taste more like strawberries. I had to try this, because it seemed just too weird. I made this yesterday, intending to have it after letting it marinate an hour, but I ended up having it today (refridgerated overnight). It was basically 3/4 liquid, 1/4 strawberries today, not as good as yesterday, but still so good. So sweet. I am willing to bet, though, that a good quality balsamic is essential. I spooned it over fresh ice milk that I just made. Added the leftover liquid to the remaining ice milk -- fantastic and very pretty. Next time I have substandard, anemic strawberries, I will try this to liven them up. If you love strawberries, you owe it to yourself to try this.

